Part (f)

We can see that even though the value of covaribility was approximately the same for the four quartets, the graphs for all of them are totally different. The first one is a simple linear relationship, second one is like an inverted U shape, third one is linear but is off by an oulier, and fourth is parallel to y axis along with a significant outlier. This emphasizes on the importance of data visualization for statistical analysis and proves why we cannot just depend on summary statistics to derive conclusions.
